<br>
Their words did not change her emotions at all.  She knew of her husband's actions, she was not an ignorant woman.  A cynical look fell across her face as she began to speak.<br>
<br>
&quot;My dear Goddesses, I know of what you speak.  I am not a weak and ignorant Goddess.  I am slightly offended that you would think that.  But I hold nothing against you both, and I do not let the offense get to me.<br>
<br>
You forget, it was Poseidon who wanted me.  I had my eyes on those of my neried race, but him, ruling over the one thing I love, intrigued me.  As long I have my sea, he can have his affairs.  For I know I can not give him all he deserves, especially since I do not love him enough,&quot; she glances at Eris and then back to Athena, &quot;as some women do.  My passion is with the sea, and nothing else.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Oh, and I am truly sorry for my husband's actions against your will, Athena, but you must understand, he is a man.  And you do have an intriguing air around you.&quot;<br>
<br>
With that, Amphitrite sat back in her chair, awaiting their response. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#003366><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=daughterofshylock>Daughter of Shylock</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.picturesof.net/_wallpaper/rose_Dsc08151_WP.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Golden Warrior</span><br>  Posts: 420<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/19/03 5:22 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=316.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> ...</span><hr size=1> Tisiphone smirked lightly.<br>
<br>
Alecto looked to Megaera and smiled.<br>
&quot;You have to admit, she has a pride that's. . .honorable.&quot;<br>
<br>
Megaera nodded and then looked to Tisiphone.<br>
&quot;Yes, but it's not her we're after. Posiedon loves his wife dearly, as she stated. Even though his affairs say otherwise, how would he feel if she loathed him?&quot;<br>
<br>
Tisiphone whispered in Amphitrite's ear, so softly that the other Gods could not hear her and be affected by her powers.<br>
&quot;My husband is not worthy of my presence in his castle. His affairs are as sickening as his brother Zeus when he sleeps at a mortals bedside.&quot;<br>
<br>
Tisiphone smirked and waited for Amphitrite to repeat the words. . .and believe them for sanity's sake. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xgoddessathenax>xGoddess Athenax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess of Wisdom and War</span><br>  Posts: 23<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/20/03 7:24 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=316.topic&index=16>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.hometown.aol.com/amznqyakut1/images/goddessathena1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Oh and so be it.</span><hr size=1> Athena smirked getting the response she expected. She waited for Tisiphone to do her magick, and calmy strolled towards the wall behind her. <br>
<br>
&quot;So my intriguing air excuses an attempt on my honour?&quot;, she said almost growling.<br>
<br>
The War Goddess placed her ivory hands on the great chains that dangled from hooks. They were, of course, no ordinary chains, they were forged by the smithy god himself.<br>
<br>
&quot;Well, I suppose you have given your nice point...&quot;, she turned around hissing those last few words. Red stripes, once again slithered across her raven orbs, before fading.<br>
<br>
She reveled in the fact that her plan was going so well.... <p>_.- Goddess Athena, Goddess of Wisdom, War, the arts, and crafts -._<br>
