<br>
The Goddess had never cried like this before, other than the time she was taken from her family.  She ignored Athena's words, focusing on the insanity that the new emotions were driving her towards.  Drowning in her own sea of pain, she ignored all of the things around her, not even noticing Athena going for the Chains of Hephestus.  She didn't care what the Warrior Goddess was to do to her.  The pain from them could not add up to the pain that the Furie helped her understand.  The pain that was brought to her by her husband.  She now understood.<br>
<br>
She threw her head back, another tear falling down her cheek, wishing for the pain to desipate like her sanity just had.  Her pale lips parted open, allowing a whince to recede threw her pearl white teeth.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#336699><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bamazonsunite.showUserPublicProfile?gid=xgoddessathenax>xGoddess Athenax</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Goddess of Wisdom and War</span><br>  Posts: 24<br> <font color=#FFFF33>(5/23/03 4:54 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/famazonsunitefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=316.topic&index=18>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.hometown.aol.com/amznqyakut1/images/goddessathena1.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Capture</span><hr size=1> The war goddess made her way over to Amphitrite's side quickly binding her with the divine chains. She made them tight before stepping back to look to the Furies.<br>
